The paper discusses the need for interpretable machine learning models in healthcare and provides an overview of interpretability approaches and examples of practical interpretability in healthcare. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses healthcare-related outcomes and decision-making, which suggests that it could also belong to the Cybernetics (cs.CY), Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
